$interpreted: Leah: Ugh, why did it have to rain now...all this rain is washing away the scent of the root, can't quite smell it now...
Leah: But it should be around here?
Leah: Ugh, I saved money to come study at Rune Academy for a chance at a better life, not to do stupid chores like this!
Leah: When I become a Rune sorcerer, I'll definitely make tons of money. I'll live in a big house with Lio and have servants feed me when I eat.
Leah: Only thing I'll need to worry about is how I'm going to enjoy life, and that's it!
Leah: ...Hmm? This smell...
Leah: Nice, the scent is just nearby! Haha, see ya annoying seniors~ You guys are gonna get expelled~
Leah: Damnit, stop getting in my way!
Leah: What the...!?
Annie: Yikes! Don't come near me!
Betty: HELP!
Cara: Mama!
Leah: Those idiots, didn't they walk towards the west? Just how lost do you have to get to end up here...
Leah: Hmm, is that!?
Leah: Didn't think that they would find the Tana Root first, but I guess it's now mine.
Leah: Lucky~

Leah: Well, now that I've gotten the Tana Root, 
I should return to the Academy.
Leah: As long as I pretend I never ran into them, everything will be a-ok.
Leah: Hmph, when we were suffering in the Slums, rich folks like them never bothered to lift a finger for us.
Leah: Why should I save them now?
Lio: Sis~ what are you going to do after you become a rune sorcerer?
Leah: Make lots of money of course. Then leave the Slums to live a good life.
Lio: Then will you protect the weak and defeat the bad guys?
Leah: That sounds pretty darn cool too...alright. From now on, if I see people in need, I will always help.
Lio: Sis, you are so cool!
Leah: However, my services certainly come at a price!
Leah: Just kidding! Heroes don't ask for money!
Lio: Yeah~ My sister is a hero!
Leah: Of course, I am your big sister after all!
Leah: Can't even handle a wimpy monster, I'm going to get all of you back to Headmaster Ceres for some serious lecturing!
